Let \(f: \mathbb{Z} \rightarrow \mathbb{Z}\) be a function defined by 
\[f(n) = \left\{ \begin{aligned} 
&2n+1, && \text{if } n \text{ is even} \\
&3n+1, && \text{if } n \text{ is odd}
\end{aligned} \right.\]
and let \(g: \mathbb{Z} \rightarrow \mathbb{Z}\) be a function defined by 
\[g(n) = \left\{ \begin{aligned} 
&n+2, && \text{if } n \text{ is even} \\
&2n+1, && \text{if } n \text{ is odd}
\end{aligned} \right.\]

The French journalist has to cover \(n\) sporting events in a year. The number of articles he writes each day is modeled by the function \(f(n)\), and the number of photographs he takes is modeled by the function \(g(n)\). He noticed that the number of articles and photographs he has on the \(n\)th day are equal for some values of \(n\). 

Find all integers \(n\) such that \(f(n)=g(n)\).
